{"TopicId":128416,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Why I really appreciate the Kerbal players here","CreatedByName":"RocketBlam","CreatedById":103420,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-22T07:25:36Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"RocketBlam","CreatedById":103420,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-22T07:25:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027re the only group of people I know who understand why the SpaceX first stage landing is an entirely different deal than the Blue Origins landing, because you understand how much different \u0022in space\u0022 is from \u0022in orbit\u0022. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t have to explain it to you. You all know already. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-12-22T07:26:09Z\u0022 title=\u002212/22/2015 07:26  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 22, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by RocketBlam\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Temstar","CreatedById":24430,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-22T07:29:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou don\u0027t work for SpaceX do you?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RocketBlam","CreatedById":103420,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-22T07:32:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNnnope... sure don\u0027t. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dafni","CreatedById":149636,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-22T08:35:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hear you. It is indeed quite refreshing when you can talk the space talk without having to explain very basic stuff first.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snarfster","CreatedById":80347,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-22T09:20:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBefore KSP I thought I knew orbital mechanics, with a calculator.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter a good number of hours crashing into things, getting lost in space and who knows what kind of mishaps, my understanding has massively improved.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll leave this here. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.explainxkcd.com/wiki/images/e/e2/orbital_mechanics.png\u0022 alt=\u0022orbital_mechanics.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Farex","CreatedById":126838,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-22T09:54:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut of course. It\u0027s an entirely different kind of flying... all together.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"selfish_meme","CreatedById":125899,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-22T10:47:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually neither goes to space, the SpaceX one has to slow down because it is boosting the second stage towards orbit so it had horizontal velocity to lose and it had to wait for the launchpad to catch up\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GoSlash27","CreatedById":111526,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-22T11:51:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222332411\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022128416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221450778081\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022126838\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Farex\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Farex said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut of course. It\u0027s an entirely different kind of flying... all together.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s an entirely different kind of flying.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Starhawk","CreatedById":131400,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-22T11:53:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222332411\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022128416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221450778081\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022126838\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Farex\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Farex said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut of course. It\u0027s an entirely different kind of flying... all together.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s an entirely different kind of flying.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"softweir","CreatedById":2795,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-22T12:20:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222332440\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022128416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221450781226\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022125899\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022selfish_meme\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, selfish_meme said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually neither goes to space, the SpaceX one has to slow down because it is boosting the second stage towards orbit so it had horizontal velocity to lose and it had to wait for the launchpad to catch up\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe OP\u0027s point is that the \u003Cem\u003Epayload \u003C/em\u003Egot to space.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"selfish_meme","CreatedById":125899,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-22T13:13:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222332518\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022128416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221450786858\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00222795\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022softweir\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n50 minutes ago, softweir said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe OP\u0027s point is that the \u003Cem\u003Epayload \u003C/em\u003Egot to space.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt maybe, its not what he said though, so how can I or you know what he meant. It doesn\u0027t matter though, regardless we all know that it is very different to lob a capsule straight up as opposed to putting a bus in orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-22T13:41:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222332440\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022128416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221450781226\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022125899\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022selfish_meme\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, selfish_meme said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually neither goes to space, the SpaceX one has to slow down because it is boosting the second stage towards orbit so it had horizontal velocity to lose and it had to wait for the launchpad to catch up\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBoth go to space, they both cross the Karman line.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sean Mirrsen","CreatedById":3873,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-22T14:03:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, the difference is in the mass, payload mass delivered to separation, and the horizontal velocity attained before returning, most of all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NecroBones","CreatedById":105424,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-22T15:00:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222332339\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022128416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221450769361\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002224430\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Temstar\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, Temstar said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou don\u0027t work for SpaceX do you?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI saw on the Space subreddit recently that there was a \u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.spacex.com/careers/position/8164\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ejob opening at SpaceX\u003C/a\u003E that we could all aspire to. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u00A0 I feel fairly confident that even though I work in a technical field, that\u0027s probably the only job there that I\u0027d be qualified for. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs an aside, XKCD\u0027s \u0022What If\u0022 article about the difference between SPACE and ORBIT is really, really good to share with people when they don\u0027t get the difference, in terms of velocity:\u00A0 \u003Ca href=\u0022https://what-if.xkcd.com/58/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EOrbital Speed\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso this goes into the differences a bit between the two rockets:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/b8c7RUjNFDo?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-12-22T15:02:24Z\u0022 title=\u002212/22/2015 03:02  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 22, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by NecroBones\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Farex","CreatedById":126838,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-22T15:37:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat I don\u0027t understand is why rocket *scientists* still use the imperial system, in presentations even. It\u0027s highly impractical and does not follow a logic whatsoever, just\u00A0arbitrarily defined nonsense for measurement for use during the colonial times of the british people.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there actually a benefit for using the imperial system in science? \u0026lt;- this is a serious question, because I just don\u0027t get it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n@GoSlash and Starhawk\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snarfster","CreatedById":80347,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-22T16:17:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe way I always understood that, it\u0027s due to the maritime origin of travel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShips -\u0026gt; Aircraft -\u0026gt; Spacecraft.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pincushionman","CreatedById":98495,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-22T16:19:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222332666\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022128416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221450796451\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105424\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NecroBones\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, NecroBones said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI saw on the Space subreddit recently that there was a \u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.spacex.com/careers/position/8164\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ejob opening at SpaceX\u003C/a\u003E that we could all aspire to. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u00A0 I feel fairly confident that even though I work in a technical field, that\u0027s probably the only job there that I\u0027d be qualified for. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u2026\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI love how even \u003Ci\u003Ethat\u003C/i\u003E position has\u00A0ITAR requirements.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"swjr-swis","CreatedById":152460,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-22T16:26:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222332497\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022128416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221450785239\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022131400\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Starhawk\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Starhawk said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s an entirely different kind of flying.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd stop calling me Shirley.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NecroBones","CreatedById":105424,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-22T16:41:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222332774\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022128416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221450801561\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152460\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022swjr-swis\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, swjr-swis said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd stop calling me Shirley.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRoger, Roger. Vector, Victor.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sean Mirrsen","CreatedById":3873,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-22T16:50:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222332666\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022128416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221450796451\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105424\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NecroBones\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, NecroBones said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs an aside, XKCD\u0027s \u0022What If\u0022 article about the difference between SPACE and ORBIT is really, really good to share with people when they don\u0027t get the difference, in terms of velocity:\u00A0 \u003Ca href=\u0022https://what-if.xkcd.com/58/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EOrbital Speed\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs an aside to that aside, I consider that the \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Eworst\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/em\u003E article of the entire What If series. For the reason that it took one facet of the questions mentioned, and ran with it without answering the actual questions.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nIndeed two of the three questions listed imply having to control the speed of reentry, and the first question explicitly proposes slowing down. So naturally the entire article is devoted to saying how going into space means going fast, and no word on whether slowing down would be a valid way of avoiding the need for a heatshield.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lordlundar","CreatedById":81040,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-22T18:44:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222332701\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022128416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221450798621\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022126838\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Farex\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Farex said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat I don\u0027t understand is why rocket *scientists* still use the imperial system, in presentations even. It\u0027s highly impractical and does not follow a logic whatsoever, just\u00A0arbitrarily defined nonsense for measurement for use during the colonial times of the british people.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there actually a benefit for using the imperial system in science? \u0026lt;- this is a serious question, because I just don\u0027t get it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n@GoSlash and Starhawk\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell there was an effort to switch to metric in the 90\u0027s (or late 80\u0027s can\u0027t remember which) as the first step in converting the entire United States to metric. To say the effort didn\u0027t pat out well is a bit of an understatement. Remember the mars climate orbiter? How because of a conversion error it ended up buried\u00A0into the mars surface instead of orbiting? yeah, similar cases. Between the mistakes and bureaucracy it was deemed such a colossal failure that NASA went back to straight imperial and it stopped the conversion project entirely.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-22T19:00:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222332941\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022128416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221450809846\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002281040\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022lordlundar\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, lordlundar said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell there was an effort to switch to metric in the 90\u0027s (or late 80\u0027s can\u0027t remember which) as the first step in converting the entire United States to metric. To say the effort didn\u0027t pat out well is a bit of an understatement. Remember the mars climate orbiter? How because of a conversion error it ended up buried\u00A0into the mars surface instead of orbiting? yeah, similar cases. Between the mistakes and bureaucracy it was deemed such a colossal failure that NASA went back to straight imperial and it stopped the conversion project entirely.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNASA is fully metric internally now, has been since 2007. They only use Imperial for public presentations to US audiences.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"swjr-swis","CreatedById":152460,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-22T19:38:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222332957\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022128416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221450810816\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002212858\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Red Iron Crown\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n37 minutes ago, Red Iron Crown said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNASA is fully metric internally now, has been since 2007. They only use Imperial for public presentations to US audiences.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmm. So they are bigger on the inside than on the outside...?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-22T19:39:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222332334\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022128416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221450769136\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022103420\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RocketBlam\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, RocketBlam said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027re the only group of people I know who understand why the SpaceX first stage landing is an entirely different deal than the Blue Origins landing, because you understand how much different \u0022in space\u0022 is from \u0022in orbit\u0022. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t have to explain it to you. You all know already. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d like this if I hadn\u0027t exceeded 25...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mighty1","CreatedById":95750,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-22T19:55:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222332701\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022128416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221450798621\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022126838\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Farex\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Farex said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat I don\u0027t understand is why rocket *scientists* still use the imperial system, in presentations even. It\u0027s highly impractical and does not follow a logic whatsoever, just\u00A0arbitrarily defined nonsense for measurement for use during the colonial times of the british people.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there actually a benefit for using the imperial system in science? \u0026lt;- this is a serious question, because I just don\u0027t get it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n@GoSlash and Starhawk\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOf course there is. Just look how great it worked for the Mars Climate Orbiter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}